com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.mashup

Class SCUIXAPIMashup

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.mashup.SCUIXAPIMashup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISCUIMashup
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SCUIPaginatedXAPIMashup

    public class SCUIXAPIMashup
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISCUIMashup
    This is implementation for ISCUIMashup, which can be used to invoke XAPIs. XAPI meta data is read from Mashup meta data. Mashup definition should contain 'xapi' element, which will be invoked via APIManager.

    Sample Mashup XML should look like this: 
     <mashup id ="mashupId" transactional="true" resourceId="DUMMY_RES_ID">
 <classInformation name="com.sterlingcommerce.ui.web.platform.mashup.SCUIXAPIMashup" />
 <appInfo>
        <!-- Some other info can be put here which is not overridable by extension. -->
 </appInfo>
 <appInfo/>
        <xapi Name="getQueryTypeList" OutputNode="QueryTypeList">
        <Input>
                <QueryType/>
        </Input>
        <Template>
                <QueryTypeList>
                        <QueryType QueryType="" QueryTypeDesc=""/>
                </QueryTypeList>
        </Template>
 </xapi>
 </mashup>
    asmishra

      • execute

        public final java.lang.Object execute(java.lang.Object input,
                                      SCUIMashupMetaData mashupMetaData,
                                      SCUIContext uiContext)
        Execute method expects input to be of type Element. If input is not null and is not of type Element, SCUIMashupException will be thrown.

        Actual XAPIs are called using APIManager. APICall is created based on 'xapi' child element of mashup metadata xml. If no 'xapi' child element is found, a SCUIMashupException will be thrown.

        If API call throws an XMLExceptionWrapper, same exception will be thrown if mashup is set not to ignore exceptions.

        This method is final; and can not be extended. Internally this method calls these protected methods - #massageInput(Element, SCUIMashupMetaData, SCUIContext) and #massageOutput(Element, SCUIMashupMetaData, SCUIContext). These methods can be extended by any class extending this particular class. input input should be of type Element mashupMetaData uiContext output from API call. Returned Object will be of type Element
        Specified by:
        execute in interface ISCUIMashup
